## LAW 3 — ProTable Usage

### 3.1 — Column Definitions

```typescript
// ✅ REQUIRED: typed column array
const columns: ProTableColumn<UserRow>[] = [
  { id: 'name', field: 'name', title: 'Name', sortable: true, minWidth: '120px' },
  {
    id: 'actions',
    title: 'Actions',
    align: 'center',
    width: '160px',
    render: ({ row }) => (
      // ✅ TSX — MANDATORY for VNode cell output
      <div class="row-center gap-xs">
        <Button v-auth="['system:user:edit']" size="small" label="Edit" onClick={() => openEdit(row)} />
        <Button v-auth="['system:user:delete']" size="small" severity="danger" label="Delete" onClick={() => confirmDelete(row)} />
      </div>
    ),
  },
]
```

For tables with **>3 columns**, columns MUST live in a separate file:

```
src/views/system/user/
├── index.vue
├── configs/
│   └── columns.tsx    ← column definitions here
└── hooks/
    └── useUserTable.ts
```

### 3.2 — HeightMode

| Scenario | `height-mode` | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Full-page data grid | `"fill"` | Standard for business views |
| Fixed-size embed | `"fixed"` | Requires `:height="'400px'"` |
| Content-driven | `"auto"` | Default |

NEVER set explicit pixel height on the ProTable wrapper via inline style.

### 3.3 — TSX Cell Renderers

```tsx
// ✅ REQUIRED: TSX
render: ({ row }) => <Tag severity={row.active ? 'success' : 'danger'} value={row.status} />,

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: h() function
render: ({ row }) => h(Tag, { severity: 'success' }),

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: string HTML return
render: ({ row }) => `<span class="text-green-500">${row.status}</span>`,
```

### 3.4 — Standard Server-Mode Pattern

```vue
<ProTable
  :columns="columns"
  :data="tableData"
  :loading="loading"
  :total="total"
  height-mode="fill"
  server-mode
  @load="fetchData"
/>
```

ProTable manages PrimeVue DataTable's `scrollable`/`scrollHeight` internally — do NOT pass these directly.

