## LAW 5 — RBAC Enforcement

### 5.1 — `v-auth` is Mandatory for All Action Elements

Every privileged action button/icon **MUST** use `v-auth`. Using `v-if` with permission strings is FORBIDDEN.

```vue
<!-- ✅ REQUIRED -->
<Button v-auth="['system:user:create']" label="New User" />
<Button v-auth="['system:user:edit']" label="Edit" />
<Button v-auth="['system:user:delete']" severity="danger" label="Delete" />

<!-- ✅ Array = OR logic: any one permission grants access -->
<Button v-auth="['system:user:edit', 'system:user:manage']" label="Manage" />

<!-- ❌ FORBIDDEN -->
<Button v-if="userStore.permissions.includes('system:user:edit')" label="Edit" />
<Button v-if="hasPermission('system:user:edit')" label="Edit" />
```

### 5.2 — Programmatic Checks via `useAuth()`

```typescript
const { hasAuth, hasAllAuths, hasRole } = useAuth()

// Single permission or OR logic (array)
const canEdit = computed<boolean>(() => hasAuth('system:user:edit'))
const canManage = computed<boolean>(() => hasAuth(['system:user:edit', 'system:user:manage']))

// AND logic — all permissions required
const canFullAccess = computed<boolean>(() => hasAllAuths(['system:user:edit', 'system:user:delete']))
```

### 5.3 — Permission String Convention

`module:entity:action` format:

| Action | String |
|---|---|
| Create | `system:user:create` |
| Edit | `system:user:edit` |
| Delete | `system:user:delete` |
| Export | `system:user:export` |
| Import | `system:user:import` |
| Batch | `system:user:batch` |

