## LAW 6 — Scroll & Virtual Scroll

### 6.1 — Fill Mode for Full-Page Grids

```vue
<ProTable height-mode="fill" server-mode @load="fetchData" ... />
```

### 6.2 — Virtual Scroll for High-Volume Local Data

For 1,000+ row local datasets (no server paging):

```vue
<ProTable :data="largeList" :virtual-scroll="true" :pagination="false" height-mode="fill" />
```

**CONSTRAINT:** `virtual-scroll`, `pagination`, and `infinite-scroll` are mutually exclusive. Never enable two simultaneously.

---

## Anti-Pattern Quick Reference

| Pattern | Status | Correct Alternative |
|---|---|---|
| `<table><tr><td>` in views | ❌ FORBIDDEN | `<ProTable :columns :data />` |
| `<form><input>` in business views | ❌ FORBIDDEN | `<ProForm :schema />` |
| Bare `overflow-auto` | ❌ FORBIDDEN | `<CScrollbar>` |
| `padding: 16px` inline | ❌ FORBIDDEN | `p-md` |
| `background: #fff` / raw hex | ❌ FORBIDDEN | `bg-card` |
| `text-gray-*`, `bg-blue-*` | ❌ FORBIDDEN | Semantic tokens (`text-muted-foreground`, `bg-primary`) |
| `v-if` for permissions | ❌ FORBIDDEN | `v-auth="['perm:string']"` |
| `h()` in cell renderers | ❌ FORBIDDEN | TSX `render: ({ row }) => <Tag />` |
| Columns >3 inline in component | ❌ FORBIDDEN | `configs/columns.tsx` separate file |
| Schema >4 fields inline | ❌ FORBIDDEN | `schemas/formSchema.ts` separate file |
| `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3` on ProForm | ❌ FORBIDDEN | `span: { xs: 12, md: 4 }` on field schema |
| `material-elevated` on view root wrapper | ❌ FORBIDDEN | `col-stretch` or `layout-container` on root, `material-elevated` on inner sections |
| `virtual-scroll` + `pagination` both true | ❌ FORBIDDEN | Pick one mode only |
